title: Video | Uttar Pradesh News | Varanasi: Flood Situation Worsens; Relief, Rescue Efforts In Full Swing - NDTV
article_text: The flood situation in Varanasi has worsened as the Ganga river continues to rise steadily. Water levels are nearing the danger mark, with all 84 ghats now submerged and the river rising rapidly every hour. According to officials, backflow in the Varuna river, a minor tributary of the Ganga has flooded 12 urban wards along its banks, leaving homes and streets waterlogged and forcing evacuations. The District Administration, Police, NDRF, and SDRF teams are working together on rescue and relief operations.

title: Video | UP Flood | Low-lying Areas In Kanpur Dehat, Prayagraj Inundated As Ganga And Yamuna Continue To Rise - NDTV
article_text: The Yamuna continues to rise causing widespread waterlogging and flood-like conditions in several villages of Kanpur Dehat and neighbouring districts of Uttar Pradesh, Villagers in affected areas say this is a recurring problem which arises every year. They also allege that the administration has failed to respond to the situation.

title: Agency News | ⚡Monsoon Death Toll Rises to 179, Rain-Related Deaths Cross 100-Mark in Himachal Pradesh - LatestLY
article_text: According to the State Disaster Management Authority (SDMA), out of the total 179 people deaths in Himachal Pradesh, 101 deaths were directly caused by rain-related disasters such as landslides, flash floods, and lightning strikes, while 78 people were killed in road accidents exacerbated by treacherous weather and damaged roads.

title: Video | Streets Waterlogged After Heavy Rain In Delhi, 'Yellow' Alert Issued - NDTV
article_text: Heavy rainfall lashed several parts of Delhi on Sunday, bringing relief from humidity but also leading to waterlogging in various areas across the national capital. Areas including Vijay Chowk, Connaught Place, Minto Bridge, Sarojini Nagar, AIIMS, and Panchkuian Marg witnessed intense showers.
